fr fr CURSED Array Operations Module
fr fr 
fr fr STATUS: Basic array operations work through built-in functions
fr fr The CURSED language provides excellent built-in array support:
fr fr 
fr fr - Array creation: sus arr [drip] = [1, 2, 3]
fr fr - Array indexing: arr[0], arr[1], etc.
fr fr - Array length: len(arr)
fr fr - Array types: [drip] for integers, [tea] for strings
fr fr 
fr fr Current module system limitations prevent custom function exports,
fr fr but built-in array functionality is complete and working.

sus arrayz_info tea = "Use built-in len() function and array indexing"
